article.headline: Northern Arizona 70, Alcorn State 61
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. (AP) -- Kyle Landry scored 21 points and Northern Arizona never trailed in beating Alcorn State 70-61 Tuesday in the consolation game of the Omaha Regional of the Guardians Classic. The Lumberjacks, who let a 10-point lead evaporate in about 2 1/2 minutes in their 77-67 loss to Iona in Monday's opener, also got 15 points from Kelly Golob, 12 from Ruben Boykin Jr. and 11 from Kyle Feuerbach. Feuerbach, NAU's only senior starter, had four 3-pointers Monday and hit three in the first half against Alcorn State as the Lumberjacks dominated from the start. Just more than five minutes into the game, NAU (1-1) led 16-4 and the lead increased to 32-9 before a 9-0 run helped the Braves cut the deficit to 34-20 at halftime. Alcorn State, which lost 74-40 to Creighton in the first round, had its second straight miserable shooting performance. They shot 37 percent (23-of-63), that number helped only by some late-game 3-pointers. The Braves had only nine points in the first half against Creighton and had only nine with 6:54 left in the first half against NAU. But back-to-back 3-pointers by Jerist Roberts and John Chandler keyed a brief comeback as the Braves outscored the Lumberjacks 11-2 to close the first half. NAU couldn't put the game away, but Alcorn State never cut the deficit to less than 10 points until the final seconds when the Braves made their fifth 3-pointer in the last two minutes. It was 45-34 before Golob hit a 3-pointer and then dished to Boykin for a layup to make it a 16-point lead. The Braves were led by DeAndre Jones with 19 points, including four 3-pointers. But he was the only player to reach double figures in either game. NAU shot 44 percent (20-of-45) and had a 24-6 edge in free throws. NAU's final 14 points came from the free throw line.
